{{ define "main" }}
<section class="lc-page-section">
  <header class="lc-page-header">
    <h1 class="lc-page-title">Cert browser is not configured</h1>
    <p class="lc-page-lede">This dashboard build supports the cert browser, but the audit DB connection string + witness gRPC endpoint have not been set on this install.</p>
  </header>
  <article class="lc-card">
    <h2 class="lc-card-title">Compose path</h2>
    <p class="lc-card-body">Populate the audit DB + witness env block in <code class="lc-mono">customer.env</code> and recreate the dashboard container:</p>
    <pre class="lc-codeblock"><code>LUCAIRN_DASHBOARD_AUDIT_DB_URL=postgres://lucairn_dashboard_ro:...@postgres-bridge:5432/dsa?sslmode=require
LUCAIRN_DASHBOARD_WITNESS_ENDPOINT=witness:50051
docker compose -f docker-compose.customer.yml --env-file customer.env --profile dashboard up -d --force-recreate lucairn-dashboard</code></pre>
  </article>
  <article class="lc-card">
    <h2 class="lc-card-title">Kubernetes path</h2>
    <p class="lc-card-body">Pre-create the read-only DB Secret in the lucairn namespace, then set the matching Helm values:</p>
    <pre class="lc-codeblock"><code>kubectl -n lucairn create secret generic lucairn-dashboard-audit-db \
  --from-literal=connection-string='postgres://lucairn_dashboard_ro:...@postgres-bridge:5432/dsa?sslmode=verify-full'

# In customer-values.yaml:
# dashboard:
#   auditDB:
#     connectionStringRef:
#       name: lucairn-dashboard-audit-db
#       key: connection-string
#   witness:
#     endpoint: witness.lucairn.svc.cluster.local:50051</code></pre>
  </article>
  {{ if .Flash }}<p class="lc-text-muted">{{ .Flash }}</p>{{ end }}
</section>
{{ end }}
